Requesting 1.  Copies of all documents, whether maintained in hard copy or stored electronically, bearing upon or related to the City of Chicago's lawsuits captioned: 
A) City of Chicago v. BCC Distribution, Inc., et al., Case No. 2019-CH-1756 (Circuit Court of Cook County, Illinois); 
B) City of Chicago v E-Liquid Depot et al,  Case No. 2018 CH 14183 ((Circuit Court of Cook County, Illinois); 
2. Copies of all documents regarding the City of Chicago's investigations regarding its operations bearing upon on related to the two aforementioned cases, including copies of all text messages, emails or other records of communications with Anthony C Thomas. 
3. Copies of all documents regarding any and all expenditures, costs, and funds the City of Chicago has spent on conducting its investigations and in prosecuting the two aforementioned cases; 
4. Copies of all documents, whether maintained in hard copy or stored electronically, from Mayor Emmanuel and/or Mayor Lightfoot regarding their respective decisions to bring forth the actions listed above and any and all documents; 
5.  Copies of all documents, whether maintained in hard copy or stored electronically,  between Mayor Emanuel, and/or Mayor Lightfoot and any Commissioner of the Chicago Department of Public Health (CDPH) serving between 2011-2020 including Dr. Allison Arwady, MD, MPH, regarding any matter regarding electronic cigarettes, vape products or tobacco use by persons, including teenagers, in the City of Chicago. 
6.  Copies of all documents, whether maintained in hard copy or stored electronically,  between Mayor Emanuel, and/or Mayor Lightfoot and/or any Commissioner of the Chicago Department of Public Health (CDPH) serving between 2011-2020 including Dr. Allison Arwady, MD, MPH, and any trade associations, public interest groups, non profit organizations, research institutions, hospitals, medical doctors, trade associations including but not limited to the National Association of Community Health Organizations, Tobacco Free Kids, Truth.Org, regarding, bearing or related to the City of Chicago's "toughed tobacco regulations" a described by the press below which states: 
"The Mayor’s toughened tobacco regulations give us the tools to go after tobacco retailers attempting to lure a new younger generation of tobacco users through vaping, e-cigs, and other accessories,” said BACP Commissioner Rosa Escareno. “Our goal is to protect youth and disrupt tobacco marketing strategies that uses candy flavored, cartoonish graphics, and easy online access". 
6. Copies of all documents, whether maintained in hard copy or stored electronically, including communications between BACP, and/or BACP Rosa Escareno and Mayor Emanuel and/or Mayor Lightfoot or any person, regarding or bearing upon the two aforementioned cases; 
7.  Copies of All settlement agreements or agreements of any kind between the City of Chicago and all defendants in the aforementioned cases including but not limited to the following defendants: 1.BCC Distribution Inc., d/b/a Beard Vape Co., Inc.;  2.BodyRock Products, LLC;  3.City of Vape;  4.Club Vapor USA 5.	D&FVapor Inc., d/b/a eJuice Direct; 6.DNA Vapor LLC, d/b/a Vapor DNA; 7.eCig Distributors, Inc. d/b/a eJuices.com and eLiquid.com; 8.Eightcig, L.L.C., d/b/a EightVape; 9.E-Juice Steals; 10.EJuice Vape Discounts; 11.E-Juice Vapor, Inc.; 12.EJuiceConnect.com, LLC; 13.Hype City Vapors, LLC; 14.LA Ejuice LLC d/b/a Five Star Juice; 15.Lost Art Liquids LLC; 16.MistHub, LLC; 17.Mountain Vapors, LLC; 18.One Up Vapor, LLC; 19.The Sabagh Group, LLC, d/b/a Lighter USA; 20.The Sauce LA; 21.3 Blind Mice, LLC, d/b/a AR eLiquid Co.; 22.Totally Wicked-E.Liquid (USA) Incorporated; 23.Vapecentric Inc.; 24.Vapor King; 25.Vaporider; 26.Veppo International LLC, d/b/a Veppo;27.West Coast Vape Supply, Inc.

