Requesting A. The following categories of information, in an electronic database format to be mutuully agreed upon, concerning each and every lawsuit filed pursuant to 42 U.S.C. §1983, against the City of Chicago, the Chicago Police Department ("CPD"), and/or any member of the CPD, since January 1, 2015:
(I) the name and number of the case;
(2) the date the case was filed:
(3) the name of the law fIrm and each lawyer who filed an appearance on behalf of the plaintiff;
(4) whether the defendant(s) was represented by the City Law Department or by outside counsel and if outside counsel, the name of the firm and the name of each attorney who filed an appearance on behalf of the defendant;
(5) the fees and cost paid, by week, month, or other billing period. to outside counsel;
(6) the final disposition of the case and date of that disposition;
(7) if the case went to verdict, the amount of any compensatory or punitive damages and of any attorneys' fees and costs paid to plaintiff;
(8) if the case was settled before or after a verdiet, the amount of the settlement, including any portion of that settlement that was allocated to plaintiff's attorney's fees and costs;
(9) for any payment of any verdict or settlement, the portion paid by the City of Chicago, identifying the fund from which each such portion was paid, and the portion paid by other sources including insurers or individual defendants;
(10) each settlement demand advanced by plaintiff, and the date of the demand and
(11) defendant's response to each settlement demand and the date of each response
B. For cach case identified in Paragraph A, Section 1, produce all documents that pertain to any settlement demand made by plaintiff including defendants' response.
C. Produce all documents that pertain to the appointment of outside council to represent the City of Chicago or the CPD or any Chicago Police office including, but not limited to the process for selecting outside counsel, the criteria used in selecting outside counsel, the manner in which the Chicago Law Department monitors the work of outside counsel, the strategies it uses, the pleadings it files, and the discovery it pursues.
D. All documents reflecting any assessment of risk or assessment of any settlement proposal created or communicated by or to the City Law Department or the City's outside counsel.

